text.section:
A county fiscal court may apply to the cabinet for authority to operate a vehicle emission control program. The cabinet may delegate authority when it has found that the applicant:
Has obtained approved machinery, tools, and equipment approved by the cabinet and adequate to conduct the required emission inspections;
Has provided for a sufficient number of facilities to ensure minimum waiting time for vehicles to be inspected;
Employs properly trained personnel with whom to perform the necessary inspections;
Has adopted minimum emission standards for vehicles at least as stringent as those adopted by the cabinet; and
Agrees to provide information prescribed by the cabinet concerning the implementation, administration, and operation of the vehicle emission control program.
